The paper deals with Collaborative Filtering (CF) and Matrix Factorization techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with recommendation systems, which fall under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of user cold-start, which is a specific problem in recommendation systems, and can be classified under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
